# What stays in the repo is exactly what GitHub Pages needs to render the talk:
#   optimal_annealing.html + optimal_annealing_files/   (the deck + reveal.js assets)
#   figures/*.svg, figures/fig_res_field.gif            (the plots the slides <img>)
#   header_logos.png, title_logos.png                   (the logos the slides <img>)
# plus the sources to rebuild it (optimal_annealing.qmd, _quarto.yml, theme.scss,
# _extensions/, figures/*.py, figures/fonts/, results/). Everything below is build
# cache, OS cruft, or leftovers from a previous talk -- none of it is needed for the
# page, so it is kept out of the push.

# --- macOS / editor cruft ----------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# --- Python cache from the figure scripts ------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]

# --- Quarto render cache (regenerated on every `quarto render`) ---------------
/.quarto/

# --- duplicate data folder ---------------------------------------------------
/results copy/
/results/*.md
/results/*.npz

# --- leftover style-reference deck from a previous talk (not part of this
#     project: _quarto.yml only renders optimal_annealing.qmd) -----------------
/quarto_PhD_seminar.qmd
/quarto_PhD_seminar.html
/quarto_PhD_seminar_files/
/style.scss

# --- unused template / example assets (not referenced by the deck) -----------
/images/
/my-iframe/
